<TITLE> Buddha Purnima Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 26 (bdnews24.com) -- Buddha Purnima, the biggest religious festival of the Buddhist community, will be celebrated on Thursday. The birth of the religion's founder Gautam Buddha, his attainment of perfect knowledge and death is believed to have occurred in the full moon of Baishakh. Buddha appeared on earth on this day about 2553 years ago. The day will be commemorated through peace processions, prayers and distribution of offerings like elsewhere in the world. Bangladesh's Buddhists have taken up a host of programmes to mark the big day. President Zillur Rahman, prime minister Sheikh Hasina and opposition leader Khaleda Zia in separate messages greeted the Buddhists on the occasion. Leaders of different social, political and cultural organisations also greeted them. The main programme will be held at International Buddha Bihar at Merul Badda, hosted by Bangladesh Buddhist Federation. Sources close to Buddha Bihar said the prorgramme will begin with the burning of Mongal Pradip. Other rituals like Buddha Puja (worship), Mahasangadan, Maha Astapariskardan will take place later on. Special prayers will be offered wishing peace and prosperity of all living beings on earth. Bangladesh Buddha Sangskritik Parisad will bring out a procession at 8am from Shahbagh which will end at the National Press Club. State minister for religious affairs Shahjahan Mia is expected to inaugurate the programme while Buddha Welfare Trust vice-chairman Sujan Kumar Talukdar will be present as special guest. Thursday is a public holiday on the occasion of Buddha Purnima. Educational institutions, offices, business establishments and commercial banks will remain closed on the day. bdn
